        <h1 class="legal-title">Data Handling Protocols</h1>
        <p class="legal-subtitle">How Your Information Traverses the Cosmic Currents</p>
        <p class="legal-date">Last Updated: Cycle 7, 5878 (January 2026)</p>

        <div class="legal-intro">
            <p>The Symphagos Expedition values your privacy as much as a rare sonic specimen. This document details what data we collect, why, and how it's protected.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>When you acquire a specimen, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email address</strong> — to deliver your specimens and license keys</li>
                <li><strong>Name</strong> — to address you in communications</li>
            </ul>
            <p>That's it. We keep data collection minimal by design.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>2. Data We Do NOT Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Payment information (handled entirely by Lemon Squeezy — we never see your card details)</li>
                <li>Browsing history or tracking data</li>
                <li>Location data beyond what's necessary for tax purposes</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
            <p>This website does not use cookies. No tracking, no analytics cookies, no third-party advertising cookies. Your expedition through Symphagos leaves no digital trail.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <p>Your email and name are used for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Delivering purchased specimens and license keys</li>
                <li>Providing support if you contact us</li>
                <li>Sending expedition transmissions (only if you opt in to the mailing list)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We will never sell, rent, or share your information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>5. Payment Processing</h2>
            <p>All payments are processed by <strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong>, our merchant of record. They handle:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Credit card processing</li>
                <li>Tax calculation and remittance</li>
                <li>Payment security (PCI compliant)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We never see or store your payment details. For Lemon Squeezy's privacy practices, see their <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>6. Data Storage & Security</h2>
            <p>Customer data is stored securely through Lemon Squeezy's infrastructure. We retain purchase records for accounting and support purposes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Request a copy of data we hold about you</li>
                <li>Request deletion of your data (note: this may affect your ability to re-download specimens)</li>
                <li>Unsubscribe from expedition transmissions at any time</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise these rights, contact <a href="/contact/">Expedition Communications</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
            <h2>8. Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>These protocols may be updated as our expedition evolves. Significant changes will be communicated via the website or email.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-footer">
